    Physical reasoning:
    - Retain all terms from v1 to capture linear, quadratic, interaction, exponential and logarithmic effects.
    - Add higher order strain terms (cubic) to capture strain hardening/softening more accurately.
    - Add inverse temperature term to model Arrhenius-type temperature dependence on stress (e.g., thermal activation).
    - Add a tanh term in strain to model saturation effects smoothly.
    
